{"lemma":"دِيوانِ","slug":"دِيوانِ","root":"د.#.ن","root_slug":"د-_-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/د-_-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n13504","n13505"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"register (registration book)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"collection of poetry","examples":[{"text":"دِيوَانُ جَمِيل بُثَيْنَة","english":"poetry collection of Jamil Buthayna"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"account, reckoning"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"place of account or reckoning"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"council, court, tribunal"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"gathering place, especially for men","examples":[{"text":"ذهبتُ إلى الديوان، أبعدتُ الستارة البيضاء عن التلفزيون وشغّلته.","english":"I went into the living room, removed the white curtain from the TV and put it on."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"divan"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Classical Persian دیوَان (dēwān)."},"ipa":["/diː.waːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13504","headword_ar":"دَيْوَانٌ","root":"dwn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n13505","headword_ar":"دِيوَانٌ","root":"dwn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", an arabicized word, (AO, M, Msb, &c.,) from the Pers. ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diywaAno","text_ar":"دِيوَانْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (AO, M, &c.;) [though some hold it to be of Arabic origin:] J says, (TA,) it is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diw~aAnN","text_ar":"دِوَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is substituted for one of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"s ; as is shown by its pl., (S, Msb,) which is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dawaAwiynu","text_ar":"دَوَاوِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, Msb, K;) for if the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"were radical, they would say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dayaAwiynu","text_ar":"دَيَاوِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) but accord. to IDrd and IJ, (IB, TA,) it has this latter pl. also: (M, IB, K, TA:) Sb says that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diywaAnN","text_ar":"دِيوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", though after"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", is not changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", as it is in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~idN","text_ar":"سَيِّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the former word is not inherent; that word being of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiE~aAlN","text_ar":"فِعَّالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daw~anota","text_ar":"دَوَّنْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) [i. e.] it is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daw~ana Alkutuba","text_ar":"دَوَّنَ الكُتُبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning “ he collected the writings; ” as is shown by their saying ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwayowiynN","text_ar":"دُوَيْوِينٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) which is the dim.: (Msb:) ISk says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dywAn","text_ar":"ديوان"},{"kind":"text","text":"is with kesr only ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"d","text_ar":"د"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (M;) but one says ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dayowaAnN","text_ar":"دَيْوَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also, (K,) which is mentioned by Ks, as postclassical, and by Sb; like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayoTaArN","text_ar":"بَيْطَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) the meaning is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafotar","text_ar":"دَفْتَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"register"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Shifá el-Ghaleel, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a collection of written leaves"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"papers"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forming a book, generally for registration"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (ISk, M, Mgh, * K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a register of accounts; an accountbook:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a register of soldiers and pensioners"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and others"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (IAth, K:) the first who instituted, or appointed, or arranged, such a book, (Mgh, Msb, K,) among the Arabs, (Msb,) for the prefects, or administrators, (Mgh, Msb,) and the Kádees, (Mgh,) is said to have been 'Omar: (Mgh, Msb, K: *) accord. to El-Máwardee, it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a register of what concerns the rights,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dues, of the state, relating to the acts of the government, and the finances, and the military and other administrators thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) then"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any book"},{"kind":"text","text":"was thus called: and especially the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poetry of some particular poet:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so that this meaning became [conventionally regarded as] a proper signification thereof; (Shifá el-Ghaleel, TA;) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a collection of poetry"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of a particular poet]. (TA.) [Hence,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN mino A^aholi Ald~iywaAni","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ مِنْ اَهْلِ الدِّيوَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is of those whose names are written in the register."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is of the keepers of the register;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is of the registrars."},{"kind":"text","text":"(And sometimes it has another meaning, which see below.) And hence the saying]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~iEoru diywaAnu","text_ar":"الشِّعْرُ دِيوَانُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEarabi","text_ar":"العَرَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Poetry is the register of the Arabs"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: because they used to refer to it on their differing in opinion respecting genealogies and wars or fights and the appointing of stipends or allowances from the government-treasury, like as the people of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dywAn","text_ar":"ديوان"},{"kind":"text","text":"[properly so called] refer to their"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dywAn","text_ar":"ديوان"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a case that is doubtful to them; or because it was the depository of their sciences, and the preserver of their rules of discipline, and the mine of their histories. (Har p. 263.) ―         -b2-  Afterwards, also, it was applied to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An account,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a reckoning."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Writers"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of accounts"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reckonings"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place of account"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reckoning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of writers"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of accounts"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reckonings"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (TA.) ―         -b5-  [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A council, court,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tribunal:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dasotN","text_ar":"دَسْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". Hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aholu Ald~iywaAni","text_ar":"اَهْلُ الدِّيوَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"sometimes means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people of the council, court,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tribunal."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b6-  And also, in the present day,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A long seat, formed of a mattress laid against the side of a room, upon the floor or upon a raised structure"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"frame, with cushions to lean against;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more of such mattresses &c. similarly placed."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"page_break","n":940}],"source_refs":["TA","S","Msb","IB","M","K","IAth","Mgh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}